5210fa51-93eb-4a56-b71b-a504cce94da3.31bab3f2-f8fc-4e14-a773-b3136b065b91.description=Attempts to acquire the specified lock, and sleeps until the lock is available. 
Inputs\:
   lockId - the id of the lock, maximum 255 characters.
   timeout - The maximum number of seconds this flow will run for.
  seconds - The number of seconds to sleep for between each attempt at acquiring the lock.

Responses\:
   success - if the lock has been successfully acquired.
   failure - if the lock could not be acquired.

Result\:
   Code - 0 if the operation succeeds, 1 otherwise.

Notes\:
1) The locks acquired by this operation are not reentrant. This means that 
   once a lock is acquired by a run, all subsequent attempts at acquiring 
   the same lock by the same run (or any other run) will fail.

2) Once a run terminates, all the locks that were acquired during its execution
   are automatically released.

5210fa51-93eb-4a56-b71b-a504cce94da3.3d6da3c0-83fb-496a-8d3a-1890ee64b275.description=Attempts acquisition of a lock with an id given by the value of the lockId input. 
Inputs\:
   lockId - the id of the lock, maximum 255 characters.

Responses\:
   success - if the lock has been successfully acquired.
   failure - if the lock has already been acquired.

Result\:
   there are no results.

Notes\:

1) The operation does not block waiting for a lock to become available.

2) The locks acquired by this operation are not reentrant. This means that 
   once a lock is acquired by a run, all subsequent attempts at acquiring 
   the same lock by the same run (or any other run) will fail.

3) Once a run terminates, all the locks that were acquired during its execution
   are automatically released.

5210fa51-93eb-4a56-b71b-a504cce94da3.48e3a266-6f41-c3de-3710-95a8db3151fa.description=

Synopsis\:
  This flow retrieves alias list (and if any, connected wwpns) that grep a pattern_match

1) Check for Nulls, init vars
2) Connect to HPNA (JRAS or HPNA), run alishow | grep $pattern_match
3) Output success/failure and new alias info.

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) Inputs\:
sanSwitch - IP of Brocade Switch
pattern_match - grep through search.

Results\:
 flowOutput -new alias/wwpn information, XML format.

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}

5210fa51-93eb-4a56-b71b-a504cce94da3.description=++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Synopsis

Brocade commands ran\:
-byAlias\: 
  switchshow (per fid)
  alishow | grep alias\: | grep $pattern_match_each (split by ',')
  foreach $aliasOutputOfGrep {
    alishow $aliasOutputOfGrep
    nssshow $wwpnOfAlias | grep Port Index
    if $localOnly\=False, then "nscamshow $wwpnOfAlias | grep Port Index"
  }

-byWwpn\:
  switchshow (per fid)
 nsshow | grep $pattern_match_each\\\; -A10 | grep ndex (split by ',')
  if $localOnly\=False, then "nsshow | grep $pattern_match_each\\\; -A10 | grep ndex"


 This flow\:
Prework\: Verify patternToMatch is all aliases or all Wwpns, no a combination lists allowed\!
1. Flow runs getAliasByPatternMatch OR getWwpnByPatternMatch in parallel (multi-instance), and builds success/fail list of IPs (update\: and now activeconfig/fabric info too)
2. Reports brocade/alias/wwpn if found, or error if cannot connect to IP, for each IP in input.
3. If you supply an FID, you will get results wrapped in the appropriate  tag.  If you do not supply an FID overloaded input, you will not get results wrapped in any  tag.

Inputs

    sanSwitchList - provided list of IPs to ssh into and search for alias or WWPN

   localOnly - when set to True, brocade command is "nsshow", when set to false, brocade command is "nsshow" and "nscamshow"

    patternToMatch - grep alias to find on each sanSwitch

Results

    foundPattern - Found alias/matchingWwpn on each Brocade if found, and any issue IPs if cant connect

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Unknown - Some brocades couldnt connect and/or subflows failed.
   Failure - something went wront before getAliasesByPatternMatch
